      <profileDesc>
         <abstract>
            <p><persName ref="#sheikhAlimullah">Sheikh Alimullah's</persName> proclamation describes the advent of four Maratha generals in
               district (pargana) <placeName ref="#pgDhar">Dhar</placeName> and the excessive tax and tribute demands made by their
               officials. He reports that because of these demands, many peasants had to sell all
               their possessions, and some fled. Despite this, only one-third of the 3000 rupees
               demanded in tribute was paid and the jagirdars are under obligation for the remaining
               portion.</p>
         </abstract>
