   <text>
      <body>
         <pb n="1r" facs="lf_pDas_1733_brd_ncd_r.jpg"/>
         <div xml:id="orig_div1" xml:lang="ara" type="invocation" rend="top centre">
            <p>
               بسم الله الرحمن الرحیم
               <lb rend="empty"/>مصلیاً علی النبیه الکریم </p>
         </div>
         <div corresp="#orig_div1" xml:id="trans_div1">
            <p>In the name of God, the Most Gracious, the Most Merciful
               <lb rend="empty"/>Praying on the Compassionate Holy Prophet</p>
         </div>
         <div xml:id="orig_div2" xml:lang="per" type="endorsements" rend="top">
            <p>
               <lb/><stamp type="seal"><mentioned>
                  <persName ref="#sheikhFathAhmad">شیخ فتح احمد</persName>
                  قاضی خادم شرع دین محمد
                     <date calendar="#julus">سنه
                        <num>۱۶</num>
                     </date>
                     <date calendar="#hijri-qamri">
                        <num>۱۱۴۶</num>
                     </date>
                  </mentioned></stamp><lb/>
               بند التحریر المتن بیان واقع
               <unclear>ت</unclear><note>This word is likely است, 'is'.</note>
               <lb rend="empty"/> <lb/>
               <stamp type="seal"><mentioned>
                  <persName ref="#muhammadDaim">دایم</persName>
                     <app>
                        <rdg cert="low">اجی</rdg>
                        <rdg cert="medium">قاضی</rdg>
                     </app>
                      خادم شرع محمد
                     <unclear>
                        <num>۱۱۴۲</num>
                     </unclear>
                  </mentioned></stamp><lb/>
               انچه در متن است بیان واقعه
               <lb rend="empty"/> <lb/>
               <stamp type="seal"><mentioned>مهر نیابت قاضی خادم شرع شریف
                      <persName ref="#sayyidMuhammadHanif">سید محمد حنیف</persName>
                     <date calendar="#julus">
                        <num>۱۶</num>
                     </date>
                     <date calendar="#hijri-qamri">
                        <num>۱۱۴۷</num>
                     </date>
                  </mentioned></stamp>
               <lb/> هَذَا بَیَانَ صادِق
               <g ref="#faqat">فقط</g>
            </p>
         </div>
         <div corresp="#orig_div2" xml:id="trans_div2">
            <p>
               <lb/><stamp type="seal">Round black ink seal<mentioned><persName ref="#sheikhFathAhmad">Sheikh Fath Ahmad</persName> <ref type="glossary" target="#gl_qazi">Qazi</ref>, servant of
                     the law of the faith of Muhammad,
                     <date calendar="#julus">regnal year 16</date>,
                     <date calendar="#hijri-qamri">1146 [Hijri]</date>
                  </mentioned></stamp>
               <lb/>Sworn [that] the writing of the document [is] a true declaration.
               <lb rend="empty"/> <lb/><stamp type="seal">Round black ink seal<mentioned><persName ref="#muhammadDaim">[Muhammad] Daim</persName><note>The first portion of this person's name, Muhammad, is read from the top of the seal, where it is elevated for respect and also modifying 'the law'.</note>
                  <app>
                        <rdg cert="medium">Qazi</rdg>
                        <rdg cert="low">Aji</rdg>
                     </app>
                      servant of the law of Muhammad
                     <date calendar="#hijri-qamri">
                        <unclear>1142</unclear>
                     </date>
                  </mentioned></stamp>
               <note>There appears to be a religious inscription around the border of the seal,
                  possibly including the shahada or Muslim declaration of faith.</note>
               <lb/>Whatever is in the document [is] a true declaration.
               <lb rend="empty"/> <lb/>
               <stamp type="seal">Round black ink seal<mentioned>Seal of the deputy <ref type="glossary" target="#gl_qazi">Qazi</ref>, servant of
                  the holy law, <persName ref="#sayyidMuhammadHanif">Sayyid Muhammad Hanif</persName>
                     <date calendar="#julus">16</date>
                     <date calendar="#hijri-qamri">1147</date>
                  </mentioned></stamp><lb/>
               This account is true.
               <g ref="#faqat">Nothing further.</g>
            </p>
         </div>
         <div xml:id="orig_div3" xml:lang="per" type="maintext">
            <p>
               <lb/>اشتهار میخواهد و استخبار میطلبید
               <persName ref="#sheikhAlimullah">شیخ علیم الله</persName>
                منصبدار شریک توجیه جاگیر
               <persName ref="#badakhshiKhan">بدخشی خان</persName>
                وغیره منسبداران چوکی خاص
               <lb/>و متصدی محال جاگیر
               <persName ref="#safiuddinMuhammadKhan">صفی الدین محمد خان</persName>
                وغیره منصبداران بابت دیهات پرگنه
               <placeName ref="#pgDhar">دهار</placeName>
                سرکار
               <placeName ref="#mandu">مندو</placeName>
                مضاف صوبه
               <placeName ref="#malwa">مالوا</placeName>
               <lb/>از سادات کرام و مشایخ عظام ذو الاحترام و ارباب شرع و عدالت و اعیان پرگنه مرقوم
               براینمعنی که از ابتدای
               <lb/>شروع سال
               <date calendar="#fasli">سنه
                  <num>۱۱۴۲</num>
                   فصلی</date>
                خبر آمد آمد فوج بادشاهی در
               <placeName ref="#malwa">مالوا</placeName>
                شهرت یافته بجاگیرداران و رعایا تقویت شده بود
               <lb/>و هنوز افواج بادشاهی از
               <placeName ref="#shahjahanabad">شاهجهان آباد</placeName>
                روانه نشده بود که
               <persName ref="#malharRaoHolkar">ملهار</persName>
                و
               <persName ref="#ranojiShinde">رانو جی سیندهیه</persName>
                و
               <persName ref="#anandRaoPuwar">انند راو پلنوار</persName>
                وغیره
               <lb/>چهار نفر ناسرداران غنیم لییم بجمعیت امبوه از دریای نربدا عبور نمود در محالات
               <placeName ref="#malwa">مالوا</placeName>
                در آمده جابجا مکاسه داران
               <lb/>بجمعیت کثیر سوار و پیاده ها تعین ساخته که جاگیر جاگیرداران بادشاهی ضبط کرده از
               محصول دروبست بتصرف در آرند
               <lb/>چنانچه مکاسه داران در محالات بهمین دستور بعمل آورده
               <persName ref="#naruPandit">نارو</persName>
                و
               <persName ref="#sadashivPandit">سداسیو پندت</persName>
                مکاسه داران پرگنه
               <placeName ref="#pgDhar">دهار</placeName>
                در دیهات
               <lb/>پرگنه شحنه و غله دار فرستاده عمل جاگیرداران برداشته چون عاملان و زمینداران و رعایا اتفاق نموده پیش ناسرداران
               <lb/>غنیم پیغام دادند که سابق در
               <date calendar="#fasli">سنه
                  <num>۱۱۴۱</num>
                   فصلی</date>
                منجمله
               <foreign>کهندنی</foreign>
                از جمله مال جاگیرداران
               <measure type="rate" unit="rupee" quantity="35">سریصد سی و پنجروپیه</measure>
                مقرر شده است و بعمل آمده
               <lb/>الحال هم بدستور سابق بگیرند و تتمه را بجاگیرداران وا گذارند چنانچه درین رد بدل
               دهات پرگنه بسیار زیر بار طلبانه آمدند
               <lb/>ناسرداران غنیم لییم بعد جواب سوال گفتند که الحال جاگیرداران افواج بادشاهی را
               برای کشتن مایان آورده چه سلوک
               <lb/>و صُلح در میان مایان و شما مانده است که عمل میخواهند مدتی درین روبدل گزسته و بعد
               روبدل بمکاسه داران
               <lb/>پروانگی دادند که نظر بر تردد گماشته های جاگیرداران داشته در جمع مال نصف وا
               گذارند و نصف را در وجه
               <foreign>کهندنی</foreign>
               <lb/>تحصیل کرده بگیرند مکاسه داران رعایا را شک ساخته بسختی تمام و طلبانه و وجه
               <foreign>کهندنی</foreign>
                خود تحصیل کرده گرفته چنانچه
               <lb/>رعایا اکثر دیهات تاتخم ساهوکار فروخته
               <foreign>کهندنی</foreign>
                ادا ساخته و بعض رعایاء دیهات در وصول آن سرانجام در خود ندیده
               <lb/>رو بفرار آوردند و اکثر مستاجر و مقدم برای ادای باقی در قید مکاسه دار هستند
               باوجود دادن غله موجودات تا تخم
               <lb/>ساهوکار مبلغ
               <measure type="currency" unit="rupee" quantity="3000">سه هزار روپیه</measure>
                در
               <foreign>کهندنی</foreign>
                باقی مانده بود از انجمله
               <measure type="currency" unit="rupee" quantity="1000">یکهزار روپیه</measure>
                از گماشتهای جاگیرداران منجمله
               <lb/>تحصیل عاملان گرفته تتمه را تمسک نویسانده گرفتند ازین سبب مبلغی کلی در مال
               جاگیرداران پرگنه باقی مانده هر کس که
               <lb/>ازینمعنی اطلاع و اگاهی داشته باشد مُهر گواهی خود ثبت نماید
               <foreign>کان ذلک</foreign>
               <g ref="#faqat">فقط</g>
            </p>
         </div>
         <div corresp="#orig_div3" xml:id="trans_div3">
            <p>
               <lb/><persName ref="#sheikhAlimullah">Sheikh Alimullah</persName>, <ref type="glossary" target="#gl_mansabdar">mansabdar</ref> part-owner of the <ref type="glossary" target="#gl_taujih">taujih</ref> of the
               <ref type="glossary" target="#gl_jagir">jagir</ref> of <persName ref="#badakhshiKhan">Badakhshi Khan</persName>, etc., <ref type="glossary" target="#gl_mansabdar">mansabdars</ref> of the Chauki Khas,<note>I.e. members of the special bodyguard or inner circle. See for instance Irvine p. 260 and Maathir al-Amara 838,.</note>
               <lb/>and the <ref type="glossary" target="#mutasaddi">mutasaddi</ref> of the <ref type="glossary" target="#gl_mahal">mahal</ref> of the <ref type="glossary" target="#gl_jagir">jagir</ref> of
               <persName ref="#safiuddinMuhammadKhan">Safiuddin Muhammad Khan</persName> etc., <ref type="glossary" target="#gl_mansabdar">mansabdars</ref> for the villages of <ref type="glossary" target="#gl_pargana">pargana</ref> <placeName ref="#pgDhar">Dhar</placeName>, 
               <ref type="glossary" target="#gl_sarkar">sarkar</ref>
               <placeName ref="#mandu">Mandu</placeName> belonging to <ref type="glossary" target="#gl_suba">suba</ref> <placeName ref="#malwa">Malwa</placeName>
               <lb/>wish to publicize and seek information from the kind elites and the great
               honourable <ref type="glossary" target="#gl_sheikh">sheikhs</ref> and the masters of law and justice and grandees of the said
               <ref type="glossary" target="#gl_pargana">pargana</ref>, that from the beginning
               <lb/>of the year <date calendar="#fasli">1142</date> <ref type="glossary" target="#gl_fasli">Fasli</ref>, news came that the imperial army was marching to
               <placeName ref="#malwa">Malwa</placeName>, and the <ref type="glossary" target="#gl_jagirdar">jagirdars</ref> and peasants were reassured.
               <lb/>But the imperial army had not yet set out from <placeName ref="#shahjahanabad">Shahjahanabad</placeName> when <persName ref="#malharRaoHolkar">Malhar
               [Rao Holkar]</persName> and <persName ref="#ranojiShinde">Ranoji Shinde</persName> and <persName ref="#anandRaoPuwar">Anand Rao Puwar</persName>, etc.,
               <lb/>four wicked generals and base plunderers, crossed over the river Narmada with a mob of followers. Entering the <ref type="glossary" target="#gl_mahal">mahals</ref> of <placeName ref="#malwa">Malwa</placeName>, [and]
               appointing <ref type="glossary" target="#gl_mokasadar">mokasadars</ref>
               <lb/>together with their many horsemen and foot soldiers in every place so that they
               seized the <ref type="glossary" target="#gl_jagir">jagirs</ref> of the imperial <ref type="glossary" target="#gl_jagirdar">jagirdars</ref>, they brought the entire revenues under
               their control.
               <lb/>Just as the <ref type="glossary" target="#gl_mokasadar">mokasadars</ref> implemented their work in the <ref type="glossary" target="#gl_mahal">mahals</ref>, accordingly, <persName ref="#naruPandit">Naru</persName>
               and <persName ref="#sadashivPandit">Sadashiv Pandit</persName>, <ref type="glossary" target="#gl_mokasadar">mokasadars</ref> of <ref type="glossary" target="#gl_pargana">pargana</ref> <placeName ref="#pgDhar">Dhar</placeName>,
               <lb/>sent a <ref type="glossary" target="#gl_shahna">shahna</ref> and <ref type="glossary" target="#gl_ghalledar">ghalledar</ref> to the
               villages of the <ref type="glossary" target="#gl_pargana">pargana</ref> and dismissed the <ref type="glossary" target="#gl_amil"><app><rdg cert="high">amil</rdg><rdg cert="low">amils</rdg></app></ref> of the <ref type="glossary" target="#gl_jagirdar">jagirdars</ref>.
               When the <ref type="glossary" target="#gl_amil">ʿamils</ref>, <ref type="glossary" target="#gl_zamindar">zamindars</ref> and peasants jointly represented in front of the wicked
               generals and plunderers
               <lb/>that before, in the year <date calendar="#fasli">1141 <ref type="glossary" target="#gl_fasli">Fasli</ref></date>, the total of the <ref type="glossary" target="#gl_khandani">khandani</ref> was was fixed as
               <measureGrp><measure type="currency" unit="rupee" quantity="35">thirty-five rupees</measure> per <measure type="currency" unit="rupee" quantity="100">one hundred</measure></measureGrp> out of all the taxes
               of the <ref type="glossary" target="#gl_jagirdar">jagirdars</ref>, and carried out
               accordingly.
               <lb/>Now too, they shall take according to prior custom, and give the remainder to
               the <ref type="glossary" target="#gl_jagirdar">jagirdars</ref>. Consequently, the villages of the
               <ref type="glossary" target="#gl_pargana">pargana</ref> came under the great weight of the [revenue] demand during this transition.
               <lb/>After a conversation, the wicked generals and base invaders
               said, 'The <ref type="glossary" target="#gl_jagirdar">jagirdars</ref> brought the imperial armies to kill us. What rule
               <lb/>and compact remains between you and us that we wish to put into action?' At a
               previous moment in this transition and after the transition,
               <lb/>they gave permission to the <ref type="glossary" target="#gl_mokasadar">mokasadars</ref> to take care of the
               resistance of the agents of the <ref type="glossary" target="#gl_jagirdar">jagirdars</ref>, hand over half the
               taxes, and collect and take the other half as <ref type="glossary" target="#gl_khandani">khandani</ref>.
               <lb/>The <ref type="glossary" target="#gl_mokasadar">mokasadars</ref> made the peasants doubtful, and collected the entire [revenue] demand and the amount of their own <ref type="glossary" target="#gl_khandani">khandani</ref> with strictness.
               <lb/>So the peasants of most villages sold everything to the <ref type="glossary" target="#gl_sahukar">sahukar</ref> in order to pay
               the <ref type="glossary" target="#gl_khandani">khandani</ref>, and some peasants of the villages did not see an end for themselves in
               the collection of taxes
               <lb/>and absconded. And many merchants and <ref type="glossary" target="#gl_muqaddam">muqaddams</ref> are imprisoned by the <ref type="glossary" target="#gl_mokasadar">mokasadars</ref>
               for their arrears. Despite giving all the grain there was to
               <lb/>to the <ref type="glossary" target="#gl_sahukar">sahukar</ref>, a sum of <measure type="currency" unit="rupee" quantity="3000">three thousand rupees</measure> was left of the <ref type="glossary" target="#gl_khandani">khandani</ref>; 
               of this, <measure type="currency" unit="rupee" quantity="1000">one thousand
                  rupees</measure> was taken from the agents of the <ref type="glossary" target="#gl_jagirdar">jagirdars</ref> for the collection of the <ref type="glossary" target="#gl_amil">amils</ref>; 
               <lb/>and they had a <ref type="glossary" target="#gl_tamassuk">tamassuk</ref> written for the remainder. For this reason, all the dues of the
               <ref type="glossary" target="#gl_jagirdar">jagirdars</ref> are outstanding. Anybody who has
               <lb/>information about this matter, shall affix his seal of evidence. And so it was.
               <g ref="#faqat">Nothing further.</g>
            </p>
         </div>
